## 2. The TLS Architecture Breakdown

| Layer | Recommended Tech | Primary Responsibility |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Presentation (Frontend)** | React.js / Next.js | UI/UX, Multi-language (i18n), and client-side task timers. |
| **Logic (Backend API)** | Node.js / Python | Referral commission logic, Anti-cheat filters, and Worker management. |
| **Data (Database)** | PostgreSQL / Redis | Storing the referral tree, transaction ledgers, and session caching. |

### The "Worker" Extension (Sub-Layer)
To maintain a professional speed, heavy tasks are moved to a **Background Worker Layer** (e.g., Redis/BullMQ):
* **Commission Engine:** Calculating the 3-level split ($10\% \to 5\% \to 2\%$) without slowing down the user's browser.
* **Notification Engine:** Handling mass emails and web-push alerts.

---

## 3. Core Technical Modules & Security

* **Anti-Fraud Suite:** * **Device Fingerprinting:** Identifies users even if they change IPs or use VPNs.
    * **Task Validation:** Heartbeat checks to ensure videos are actually watched.
* **Global Payments:** Integration of Stripe/PayPal for fiat and a crypto gateway (e.g., CoinGate) for USDT/BTC.
* **Scalability & Performance:**
    * **CDN (Cloudflare):** For fast global loading and DDoS protection.
    * **Audit Logs:** Immutable records of every balance change for financial integrity.
* **Database Redundancy:** Automatic "Point-in-Time" backups to prevent loss of user earning data.

